{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Basic.html#Lean.withSetOptionIn\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">withSetOptionIn</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">cmd</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Elab.Command.CommandElab</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Elab.Command.CommandElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a command elaborator `cmd`, returns a new command elaborator that\nfirst peels off and evaluates `set_option ... in ...` syntax recursively, updating the options\naccordingly, and then invokes `cmd` on the inner syntax.\n\nThis is expected to be used in linters, after elaboration is complete. It is not appropriate for\nordinary elaboration of outer `set_option`s, since it\n* does not update the infotrees with info for the `set_option` commands\n* silently ignores failures in setting the given options (e.g. we do not error if the option is\n  unknown or the wrong type of value is provided), as these should have been reported during\n  original elaboration.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Linter/Basic.html#Lean.withSetOptionIn","kind":"opaque","line":25,"name":"Lean.withSetOptionIn","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Linter/Basic.lean#L25-L46"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Command","Lean.Linter.Init"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Linter.Basic"}